Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is collected, used, and disclosed by [company name] ("we", "us", or "our"). We take your privacy very seriously and only collect information that is necessary to provide the products or services you request from us. In this Privacy Policy, "personal information" means information about you that can be used to identify you, such as your name, email address, or other contact information.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect personal information from you such as your name, email address, mailing address, phone number, date of birth, and other contact information when you visit our website, register for our services, or interact with us online. We may also collect information about your use of our website and services.

2. Use of Information
We may use your personal information to:

a. Provide the products or services you request from us.
b. Send you important account information, including notices about changes to our Privacy Policy.
c. Respond to your customer support requests or other information requests.
d. Send you promotions, special offers, or other information that may be of interest to you.
e. Send you messages related to disruptions, repairs, or updates to our application.
f. Analyze the usage of our application for the purpose of developing our application.

3. How We Share Information
We will not share your personal information with third parties except in the following circumstances:
a. We comply with applicable laws or legal processes, or if we believe such action is necessary to protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of others.
b. We may share information that cannot be personally identified with partners or other third parties for research or analysis purposes.
c. We take reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from damage, loss. However, we cannot guarantee the security of information that you submit to us or receive from us online. You should take steps to protect your personal information, such as using a strong password and avoiding using the same password for different accounts.

4. Your Choices
You have the choice to not provide personal information to us. However, if you choose not to provide the personal information requested by our application, you are required not to use our application, so your data is not stored in our database.
We may provide links to third-party websites, products, or services on our website. If you follow these links to third-party websites, products, or services, their Privacy Policy will apply. We are not responsible for, and do not have control over, the practices, content, and privacy policies of third-party websites or services.

5. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes to our Privacy Policy by posting the latest version of this Privacy Policy on our website and/or by sending an email to the email address or WhatsApp number registered in your account. You agree to receive emails or WhatsApp messages from us in this regard.

6. Contact Us
If you have any questions or complaints about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices in general, please contact us at 0822-30319943.

This Privacy Policy is effective as of April 8, 2023, and replaces all previous privacy policies issued by us.
